	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A Tailored Quiver can be made from a Quiver Pattern and a High Quality Cat Pelt, in a Sewing Kit. The Tailored Quiver has 6 slots, weighs 0.4, and can only hold arrows.<BR>
<BR>
The advantage of a Tailored Quiver over a Large Bag is that you save 0.6 pounds, though it has the disadvantage you can't put other stuff in it.<BR>
<BR>
The Kunark supplement suggests other quivers could be made. I tried a Sabertooth Tiger Skin and an ordinary Tiger Skin with a Quiver Pattern, and got the &quot;bad combo&quot; response.<BR>
<BR>
I had looted a Quiver of Marr from a skellie in Karnor's Castle. It held 6 and weighed only 0.1. But when I logged out/in, it disappeared (along with the arrows I had put inside).
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
